Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Name, Klenostratos.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p. 27a, 14; the apparent original entry '27a, 15' is in fact Petrie's interpretation of this piece and so has been deleted from the catalogue of stamps.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1123)
